AI Friday Season 2 – Problem Statements 
Real-Time Language Detection and Seamless Code-Switching Support 
PROBLEM STATEMENT 
Voice systems typically do not support multilingual or language-switching users effectively, often resulting in 
recognition failures when users switch languages mid-conversation. For example, Rahul’s use of Hindi-English mixed 
speech confuses the system and interrupts interactions. This limitation hampers adoption in multilingual societies and 
global markets. Current systems lack real-time language detection and smooth code-switching capabilities, causing 
broken workflows and poor user experience. The business impact includes lost engagement, reduced inclusivity, and 
market limitations. AI solutions enabling dynamic language identification and code-switching support can unlock 
natural multilingual interactions. 
Data Considerations: 
Code-switching speech datasets with Hindi-English mixtures and other bilingual samples; multilingual speech 
corpora; language detection training data; volume targeting thousands of mixed-language utterances; preprocessing 
for language segmentation and annotation; data privacy and linguistic diversity compliance; synthetic code-switching 
data generation advised. 
Consider using synthetic or anonymized data where appropriate. Ensure data quality and relevance to the problem 
context. 
SOLUTION EXPECTATIONS 
A voice recognition platform supporting real-time language detection and seamless code-switching; UI displaying 
detected language cues; backend integration with multilingual assistant APIs; measurable improvements in code
switching recognition accuracy; user guide explaining multilingual interaction features; technical documentation on 
language detection algorithms; demo illustrating smooth language transitions during conversations. 
Accessibility Impact: Benefits multilingual users and users who naturally code-switch during conversation. Expected 
outcome: users can communicate naturally without being forced into a single language or rigid interaction pattern. 
Feel free to explore creative solutions that align with the problem context and objectives. 
